    "In the NSP task, BERT uses the hidden layer of the [CLS] position as the semantic representation of the context consisting of the first component h 0 of h, and finally predicts the classifi- cation probability P of the input text through a fully connected layer: where P ∈ R 2, W p ∈ R d×2 represents the weight of the fully connected layer, and b 0 ∈ R 2 represents the bias of the fully connected layer.",
    "Classification probability P is used to calculate cross-entropy loss with the real label y.",
    "The final model parameters are updated based on this loss.",
